Class AppIdentityCredential

OAuth 2.0 credential in which a client Google App Engine application needs to access data that it owns, based on Asserting Identity to Google APIs.

Intercepts the request by using the access token obtained from AppIdentityService.getAccessToken(Iterable).

Sample usage: 

  public static HttpRequestFactory createRequestFactory(
      HttpTransport transport, JsonFactory jsonFactory, TokenResponse tokenResponse) {
    return transport.createRequestFactory(
        new AppIdentityCredential("https://www.googleapis.com/auth/urlshortener"));
  }

Implementation is immutable and thread-safe.
